<div id="settings_plugin_riskyupnpforward" class="plugin-settings">

	<div class="alert alert-warning">
		<strong>âš  Warning:</strong> Port forwarding WILL expose your OctoPrint instance to the internet and may make your network vulnerable to attacks. 
		Only enable this if you understand the risks and have secured your OctoPrint instance with a strong password and HTTPS.
	</div>

	<p>
		This plugin attempts to automatically forward a port on your router using UPnP, allowing access to OctoPrint from outside your local network.
		Configure the internal port (used by OctoPrint) and the external port (publicly visible) below.
		You'll have to restart OctoPrint in order for these settings to take effect.
	</p>

	<div class="control-group">
		<label class="control-label" for="settings_plugin_riskyupnpforward_internal_port">Internal Port</label>
		<div class="controls">
			<input type="number" id="settings_plugin_riskyupnpforward_internal_port"
				   data-bind="value: settings.plugins.riskyupnpforward.internal_port" />
			<span class="help-block">This is the port OctoPrint is running on (usually 5000 or 80).</span>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="control-group">
		<label class="control-label" for="settings_plugin_riskyupnpforward_external_port">External Port</label>
		<div class="controls">
			<input type="number" id="settings_plugin_riskyupnpforward_external_port"
				   data-bind="value: settings.plugins.riskyupnpforward.external_port" />
			<span class="help-block">This is the port that will be exposed on your router to the public internet. It's best practice to use a DIFFERENT port from your internal port.</span>
		</div>
	</div>

	<hr/>

	<div class="control-group">
		<label class="control-label" for="settings_plugin_riskyupnpforward_enable_on_startup">Enable on Startup</label>
		<div class="controls">
			<input type="checkbox" id="settings_plugin_riskyupnpforward_enable_on_startup"
				   data-bind="checked: settings.plugins.riskyupnpforward.enable_on_startup" />
			<span class="help-block">Enable automatic port forwarding every time OctoPrint starts.</span>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="control-group">
		<label class="control-label" for="settings_plugin_riskyupnpforward_remove_on_shutdown">Remove on Shutdown</label>
		<div class="controls">
			<input type="checkbox" id="settings_plugin_riskyupnpforward_remove_on_shutdown"
				   data-bind="checked: settings.plugins.riskyupnpforward.remove_on_shutdown" />
			<span class="help-block">Try to remove the port mapping when OctoPrint shuts down.</span>
		</div>
	</div>

	<hr/>

